      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:40:2",
      "text": [
        " أَنَّ أَمِيرَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) أُتِيَ بِرَجُلٍ قَدْ بَاعَ حُرّاً فَقَطَعَ يَدَهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> that Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup>, they came to him<sup>asws</sup> with a man who had sold a free man. He<sup>asws</sup> cut his hand’."
        ]
